We are experiencing issues with attachment uploads/downloads in Cloud at the moment. All attempts to do so will result in errors similar to this:
{code}
An error occured while attaching test.jpg:
com.atlassian.jira.issue.attachment.store.media.MediaApiStreamAttachmentStore$FailureMediaApiResponseException: [AttachmentUploadFailure] Could not upload temporary attachment Failure: Failure
{cause=null, reason=BAD_STATUS, message='', httpStatusCode=500}
{code}

We will provide regular updates to this via: http://status.atlassian.com/incidents/6crzl3j0xd7m

h3. Note
This bug also affects JIRA/Confluence backup creation

{panel:title=Atlassian Status: Feb 28, 2017 ~ 23:00 UTC|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3c78b5|titleBGColor=#3c78b5|bgColor=#e7f4fa}
h5. Following the stabilization of AWS service, Atlassian services have been fully restored. We apologize for the extended interruption to service and will continue to monitor our systems to ensure services remain stable.
{panel}

Atlassian is currently investigating upstream issues which are leading to degraded performance across multiple platforms including Bitbucket, HipChat, and Cloud services. We are working to mitigate these issues as quickly as possible.

Updates are made available via the following StatusPage incident: http://status.atlassian.com/incidents/cydc6gj5rrlz
